<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-16169] FencedException in commitAsync not propagated without callback</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-16169</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The javadocs for&#160;&lt;tt&gt;commitAsync()&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;(w/o callback) say:&lt;br/&gt;
@throws org.apache.kafka.common.errors.FencedInstanceIdException if this consumer instance gets fenced by broker.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
If no callback is passed into&#160;&lt;tt&gt;commitAsync()&lt;/tt&gt;, no offset commit callback invocation is submitted. However, we only check for a&#160;&lt;tt&gt;FencedInstanceIdException&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;when we execute a callback. It seems to me that with&#160;&lt;tt&gt;commitAsync()&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;we would not throw at all when the consumer gets fenced.&lt;br/&gt;
In any case, we need a unit test that verifies that the&#160;&lt;tt&gt;FencedInstanceIdException&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;is thrown for each version of&#160;&lt;tt&gt;commitAsync()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
